column1: # This file is where sequence data is maintained.
#Column 1 is the OID of the base character (a o098xxxxx in new OIDS)
#Column 2 is the sign name for the base character
#Column 3 is an integral glyph to be used for the display of the ligature
#Column 4 is a descriptive version of the glyph in which the individual
#components are the glyf variants exhibited by the integral glyph.
#This column is used by seq-final.plx to generate the glyph name: a
#glyph name consists of the base character of each glyph, a period
#(which is effectively the base character of all joiners) and a tag.
#The tag is variant number for the sequence of glyph names and is used
#as the basis for the CVnn for the glyph's ligature.
